=Adds a new data point for use by the Statistics functions=
:$$2nd S+$$
:Code: ''78'', In Help Files: ''S+''
Both register '''X''' and register '''T''' are added, as a data point. $$INV 2nd S+$$ is used to remove data point.
Before entering the data points, the user should reset to 0 the registers used by the Statistics functions as follows: $$2nd Pgm 01 sbr clr$$.
==Example==
*$$2nd Pgm 01 sbr clr 10 2nd S+$$: @@1@@
*$$20 2nd S+$$: @@2@@
*$$2nd avg$$: @@15@@
*$$inv 2nd avg$$: @@7.071067812@@
